{
    "attributes": {
        "action": " Automatically obtain a Class 2 license after 2 years of a PSV driving licence",
        "additional_details": "Many PSV licence holders cannot drive a van that has a mgw (mass gross weight) of more than 3.5t, however may drive PCV vehicles that are 14.5m in length with a mgw of 26t.\r\n",
        "background": "Many PCV vehicles are larger in size and weight than class 2 vehicles. We believe after 2 years of holding a PSV licence, you should be able to apply for and automatically obtain your Class 2 licence without having to take further tests and spend any money.",
